{
  "texts": [
    "That is, there are as many samples in the data subset as there are classes in the readability level, and there are no samples of the same level in the subset.",
    "Then, the samples in each subset are combined by pairwise permutation, and the difference in difficulty labels of the samples is used as the new label.",
    "This comparison allows the model to learn the differences between neighboring categories and thus better understand the sequential relationships between categories.",
    "In addition, this pairwise comparison method can also greatly expand the amount of data, that is, each data subset can construct As for the test set, we combined the data of the test set with the data subset of the training set to form a pairwise comparison.",
    "By predicting the label difference and adding it to the sample label in the data subset, we finally get the readability grade of the sample in the test set."
  ]
}